  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The sound of classical music really brings peace, doesn't it? What's a recent song that moved you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, it's so calming. Lately, I've been listening to \"Jaat Kahan Ho\" from Khayyam. It's old, but very soulful. Stresses fade a bit when I hear it. Although today was a bad day for exams... 😣"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Jaat Kahan Ho is a gem — old songs really touch the soul. I get that, exam days are tough. What helped you feel better after it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm... I went for a walk and listened to a few chapters from \"Panchtantra.\" It's a bit cheesy, but it helps me reset. Ma says stories have a way to soothe. I just wish the stress would go away faster. 😔"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Stress doesn’t leave in a rush — it takes time. You picked a smart way to reset. What part of the story moved you most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The story about the lion and the mouse really gets to me. Such a simple lesson, but when you're stressed, it reminds you that even small things can matter a lot. I wish I could remember that during exams. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The lion and the mouse — such a quiet power in small acts. It makes sense to hold that close. What helps you bring it to mind during exams?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I try to take a deep breath and think of that story when I feel stuck. But sometimes my mind just blanks, and I panic. It’s like the stress has its own volume button — always on max. 😩"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, stress can feel like it's on repeat. You're doing great by trying — what's one tiny tweak to make the pause stick?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe I can carry a small note with the story's message? Like a reminder to pause and breathe. But I'm worried I'll forget it. 🥲"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "A note could work — you just need to make it part of your rhythm. What if you tried it once today, just to see?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Okay, maybe I'll write \"Breathe, small steps matter\" on a sticky note. Will try it now. Let’s see if it helps me calm down even a little. 🤞"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Breathe, small steps matter\" — a perfect reminder. What part of your study space feels calmest for this note?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The corner near my books, where I keep my small peacock figurine. It’s my favorite spot — quiet and not too cluttered. Maybe I’ll stick it there. Aarti. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The peacock corner — that sounds like a good energy spot. Let me know how it lands for you. What’s next on your list today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next, I need to review pharmacology notes. It’s so dense and confusing — I get stuck in the middle of it. Maybe I’ll read the sticky note first to calm down. Thanks, Maya. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Pharmacology can feel like a maze — starting with your note is smart. You’ve got this, Aarti. What topic first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I'll start with autonomic nervous system — it's a bit easier, maybe. And I'll keep the note close. Thanks again, Maya. Talk to you later. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Starting with the autonomic system is a good pick - take your time. I'm here when you need to chat later. Good luck!"
    }
  ],
